01:21:00.423 --> 01:21:02.063
- What do you mean?

01:21:02.091 --> 01:21:06.631
- I mean honesty and openness,
no matter what.

01:21:06.662 --> 01:21:09.132
- I try!

01:21:09.165 --> 01:21:11.425
I do,
but every time, we just--

01:21:18.507 --> 01:21:21.507
I have no idea what I could say

01:21:21.544 --> 01:21:25.184
that's gonna make any difference
in this situation.

01:21:28.952 --> 01:21:32.192
- That is so you to give up.

01:21:32.221 --> 01:21:34.261
You know, just when you're
on the brink of something,

01:21:34.290 --> 01:21:37.590
you just give up.

01:21:37.626 --> 01:21:40.326
So guess what.
Now it's my turn.

01:21:47.236 --> 01:21:49.336
I'm sorry.

01:21:49.372 --> 01:21:52.512
*

01:21:54.410 --> 01:22:02.350
*

01:22:21.304 --> 01:22:23.544
- She's right.

01:22:23.572 --> 01:22:26.712
I let her down...

01:22:26.742 --> 01:22:29.682
in so many ways.

01:22:29.712 --> 01:22:33.082
- You have to tell her...

01:22:33.116 --> 01:22:36.386
what's going on
in the ivory tower.

01:22:36.419 --> 01:22:40.159
- There's nothing going on.

01:22:40.189 --> 01:22:42.289
- Is that the truth?

01:22:47.096 --> 01:22:49.766
- In a way, you know...

01:22:49.798 --> 01:22:51.998
there's a lot going on.

01:22:52.035 --> 01:22:53.635
- Yes.

01:22:53.669 --> 01:22:57.069
- Like even here, you and I,

01:22:57.106 --> 01:22:59.776
the things that we talk about,

01:22:59.808 --> 01:23:02.148
they're like...

01:23:02.178 --> 01:23:03.578
They're parts of myself

01:23:03.612 --> 01:23:09.022
that I've put aside
and literally forgotten.

01:23:09.052 --> 01:23:13.792
Like my passion, I mean,
where did that go?

01:23:13.822 --> 01:23:15.422
- Did it walk out the door?

01:23:15.458 --> 01:23:17.358
- No, I'm not putting that
on her.

01:23:17.393 --> 01:23:19.733
It's mine.

01:23:19.762 --> 01:23:21.232
It's me,

01:23:21.264 --> 01:23:22.674
and I lost it.

01:23:26.735 --> 01:23:31.035
- Then maybe it's time
for the inspired act,

01:23:31.074 --> 01:23:35.114
the preemptive strike
of the samurai.

01:23:35.144 --> 01:23:39.724
Take a stand for yourself

01:23:39.748 --> 01:23:42.148
and what you want.

01:23:45.188 --> 01:23:51.528
*

01:23:51.560 --> 01:23:53.800
- I got to go.

01:23:53.829 --> 01:23:58.729
*

01:23:58.767 --> 01:24:02.137
Thanks, Jeff.

01:24:13.549 --> 01:24:21.389
*

01:24:24.427 --> 01:24:32.367
*

01:25:14.477 --> 01:25:21.547
- Hi.

01:25:25.388 --> 01:25:27.258
- Why are you here?

01:25:29.725 --> 01:25:32.925
I want to tell you
that I feel bad for lying to you

01:25:32.961 --> 01:25:37.871
and taking advantage of you
and for not owning up,

01:25:37.900 --> 01:25:40.470
and I'm doing my best,
right now,

01:25:40.503 --> 01:25:44.443
to just keep talking

01:25:44.473 --> 01:25:50.883
and not disappear.

01:25:50.913 --> 01:25:54.753
- Do you want out?

01:25:54.783 --> 01:25:56.323
- Of--of what?

01:25:56.352 --> 01:25:57.522
- Us.

01:25:57.553 --> 01:25:59.223
- No, not in the least.

01:25:59.255 --> 01:26:00.755
- Are you sure?

01:26:00.789 --> 01:26:04.659
- It's the one thing
I'm absolutely sure of.

01:26:04.693 --> 01:26:06.303
Do you?

01:26:06.329 --> 01:26:09.229
- I don't know.

01:26:09.265 --> 01:26:11.625
I really don't.

01:26:11.667 --> 01:26:13.467
I know I don't want it
like this.

01:26:13.502 --> 01:26:15.602
- I can understand that.

01:26:17.440 --> 01:26:20.240
So why are you making
everything so miserable?

01:26:20.276 --> 01:26:24.876
- You know, it's been six years
since Bluebird,

01:26:24.913 --> 01:26:28.383
and honestly
Bluebird was shit!

01:26:28.417 --> 01:26:30.717
Each year,
it gets harder and harder.

01:26:30.753 --> 01:26:35.323
I don't know if I have
what it takes, you know,

01:26:35.358 --> 01:26:37.658
that thing, that shimmer,
you know?

01:26:37.693 --> 01:26:40.733
I don't even know if what I have
to say is relevant any more.

01:26:40.763 --> 01:26:44.503
I mean, I used to be on fire.

01:26:44.533 --> 01:26:46.243
Now I'm like a washed-up
stay-at-home.

01:26:46.269 --> 01:26:48.539
- What does that even mean?

01:26:48.571 --> 01:26:50.541
You used to be the guy
that said to me

01:26:50.573 --> 01:26:52.643
that if you could speak
to the heart of one person,

01:26:52.675 --> 01:26:55.705
it was worth it.

01:26:55.744 --> 01:26:58.554
That was Sam Tucker.

01:26:58.581 --> 01:27:01.521
*

01:27:01.550 --> 01:27:03.350
